<center><span style="font-family:Pacifico; color: white;">'''Level 703''' is the 704th level of the backrooms.</span><center>
</div>

<div style="background-color:#000000; color: white; margin:1em; padding:20px 20px; border:4px solid #ff69b4; border-radius: 30px"><span style="color:#ff69b4;"><span style="font-family:Pacifico;">

<center>
<span style="font-size:25px; font-family:Pacifico; text-shadow: 0em 0em 1.0em #ff69b4, 0em 0em 1.0em black;


 background: linear-gradient(90deg, #ff69b4, #e0569d, #ff69b4, #e0569d, #ff69b4);

             background-size: 400%; 
             -webkit-background-clip: text;
             -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
             animation: gradient 5s infinite;"> Description</span>{{Underline|ff69b4}} <center>

<div style="text-align:left;font-family:Georgia;color:#FFFFFF">

{{Blurimage|file=First_photo_taken_of_Level_-237.jpg|caption=The first photo of Level 703.}}
'''Level 703''', also known as '''"Garden of the Divine Galleries,"''' takes the form of an enormous forest with vibrant pink and purple coloration. 
The forest has properties similar to other common forests, with an abundance of different types of flowers and trees. 

Its expansion is unlimited and can range from flat areas to mountainous regions, but always maintains the only type of flora that is continuously present at '''Level 703. '''
Its climate pattern is abnormal with unstable temperatures and a high rate of radioactive waves frequently released by the sky and the flowers active in the flora. 

Its entire area is illuminated by a single, motionless solitary star in the sky, which creates strong pink lights that are responsible for releasing large quantities of strong radioactive waves throughout the entire level. Due to this unusual specification, '''Level 703''' has no celestial cycle.

As eminent as its flora is, no animal being was able to survive or reproduce at the level, leaving humans as the only species capable of enduring the current conditions.

The radiation transmitted by the level is completely lethal to any living being. However, humans seem to have higher resistance than other beings. Even with a sort of resistance, humans will still suffer serious consequences from prolonged nuclear exposure. Even though radioactive waves are lethal, they appear to cause no harm to eukaryotic plant cell systems. Furthermore, plant cellular systems, particularly flowers, appear to absorb light radiation and then adapt to also expel it at higher rates.

Until now, the cause of such lethal radiation reaching only beings with animal cells is unknown, but possible research in the future may have the answer.


</div>
</div>

<div style="background-color:#000000; color: white; margin:1em; padding:20px 20px; border:4px solid #ff69b4; border-radius: 30px"><span style="color:#ff69b4;"><span style="font-family:Pacifico;">

<center>
<span style="font-size:25px; font-family:Pacifico; text-shadow: 0em 0em 1.0em #ff69b4, 0em 0em 1.0em black;


 background: linear-gradient(90deg, #ff69b4, #e0569d, #ff69b4, #e0569d, #ff69b4);

             background-size: 400%; 
             -webkit-background-clip: text;
             -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
             animation: gradient 5s infinite;"> Spirituality</span>{{Underline|ff69b4}} <center>

<div style="text-align:left;font-family:Georgia;color:#FFFFFF">

Within the large and dense forests of '''Level 703,''' one can feel several strange feelings, probably symptoms of radiation. However, a peculiar sensation can be perceived by all individuals when present at the level.

When spending an indefinite amount of time on the level, or even just after entering it, one can feel enormous spiritual pressure coming from within the forests. This "pressure" has not yet been studied enough for concrete information to be obtained, but it does not appear to present serious consequences or mental danger to affected individuals.

The true origin of this feeling or whether it is a possible symptom of severe radioactive waves is unknown. Even with the lack of resilient information about this sensation, it was possible to discover where it could come from.


<center>
<span style="font-size:25px; font-family:Pacifico; text-shadow: 0em 0em 1.0em #ff69b4, 0em 0em 1.0em black;
 background: linear-gradient(90deg, #ff69b4, #e0569d, #ff69b4, #e0569d, #ff69b4);
             background-size: 400%; 
             -webkit-background-clip: text;
             -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
             animation: gradient 5s infinite;"> The Divine Galleries</span> <center>

The '''Divine Galleries''' are temple structures of random size and proportions rarely found in the deepest parts of '''Level 703''' forests. These structures are made of quartz-like materials and demonstrate familiar patterns from monuments in the frontrooms. The galleries always seem abandoned and sometimes destroyed, with different types of flora covering them or keeping them hidden.

{{Blurimage|file=Image taken of a Divine Gallery.png|caption=Photo taken of a Divine Gallery.|align=center}}

These structures are responsible for originating all the spiritual pressure that expands throughout the area around it. Regardless of their conditions or location, galleries are always enormous precursors of spirituality.

Due to its size, it was expected that it could serve for refugee purposes or even places to establish outposts. However, the enormous spiritual pressure from the galleries prevents anything from stepping near them, forcing anyone to take steps back.

It is not possible to know its origin or what is inside the galleries that makes this spirituality so strong. Until then, it is not recommended to go close to the temples.


</div>
</div>

<div style="background-color:#000000; color: white; margin:1em; padding:20px 20px; border:4px solid #ff69b4; border-radius: 30px"><span style="color:#ff69b4;"><span style="font-family:Pacifico;">

<center>
<span style="font-size:25px; font-family:Pacifico; text-shadow: 0em 0em 1.0em #ff69b4, 0em 0em 1.0em black;


 background: linear-gradient(90deg, #ff69b4, #e0569d, #ff69b4, #e0569d, #ff69b4);

             background-size: 400%; 
             -webkit-background-clip: text;
             -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
             animation: gradient 5s infinite;"> Entities</span>{{Underline|ff69b4}} <center>

<div style="text-align:left;font-family:Georgia;color:#FFFFFF">

Due to the dangers and environmental instabilities of the level, no entity with animal cells can exist at '''Level 703.''' On the other hand, two anomalies that do not qualify as animals could be recorded.

<div class="tabs">
<ul class="tabs__caption">
<li class="active">Flowers</li>
<li>The star</li>

</ul>
<div class="tabs__content active">


<center>
<span style="font-size:25px; font-family:Pacifico; text-shadow: 0em 0em 1.0em #ff69b4, 0em 0em 1.0em black;
 background: linear-gradient(90deg, #ff69b4, #e0569d, #ff69b4, #e0569d, #ff69b4);
             background-size: 400%; 
             -webkit-background-clip: text;
             -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
             animation: gradient 5s infinite;"> Apollum-12</span> <center>

'''Apollum-12''' is the most abundant flower species at '''level 703.''' This species of flower is supposedly the most capable of adapting to the level's radiation and its nuclear properties.

These flowers should be avoided at all costs because, for unexplained reasons, they can generate bio-chemical waves of radiation. Depending on exposure to light, the radiation produced can be more dangerous than those transmitted by '''the star.'''

{{Blurimage|file=Apollum-12.png|caption=Photo taken of a group of flowers of the Apollum-12 species.|align=center}}

After several studies on the so-called PARL phenomenon (Plant Adaptability to Lethal Radiation), some theories could be structured.

The main explanation would be the recently discovered PAG (Photocontinuous Genes Adaptation) phenomenon. This phenomenon occurs after the insertion of radioactive light into the flowers of the Apollum-12 species, which, unlike the others, have a mutated gene (codename Gene rad-phyto16), which theoretically would be capable of synthesizing radioactive light into proteins. The only explanation for this phenomenon is a possible genetic variation of Chlorophyll-R of Apollum-12, which makes it prone to receiving doses of radiation and, after removing energy from light, redirects the nuclear content using probably, mutated callose-R molecules.

This also explains that the most abundant flower species at the level is Apollum-12. It is evident that other species of flowers without the mutated phyto gene are disappearing over time. 

Other types of flora, such as trees for example, also seem to adapt to radiation, however, they do not seem to possess the gene molecule necessary for absorbing proteins or expelling bio-chemical residues.

</div>


<div class="tabs__content">

<center>
<span style="font-size:25px; font-family:Pacifico; text-shadow: 0em 0em 1.0em #ff69b4, 0em 0em 1.0em black;
 background: linear-gradient(90deg, #ff69b4, #e0569d, #ff69b4, #e0569d, #ff69b4);
             background-size: 400%; 
             -webkit-background-clip: text;
             -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
             animation: gradient 5s infinite;"> Hylophage-66</span> <center>

'''The star''', also known as '''Hylophage-66''', is an enormous celestial that remains motionless above the skies of '''Level 703''' and is proven to be the only Astro ever found. The star is also responsible for all the level's lighting, always keeping it in a "daytime state." It is heavily recommended to avoid any contact with the light produced by the star.

{{Blurimage|file=Hylophage-66.png|caption=Illustrative photo of '''The Star.'''|align=center}}

The origin of '''Hylophage-66''' is completely unknown, as is its enormous radioactive frequency. It is possible to confirm that the star is the main agent that caused '''Level 703''' to be in the state it is in today. It is not known whether the level was ever habitable or whether it could be in the future.

Due to the complete lack of knowledge, as well as the impossibility of carrying out studies on Hylophage-66, it is not possible to obtain concrete information, however, more studies may be carried out in the future.
{{Underline|ff69b4}}

The following content is confidential and can only be read by authorized personnel. Please enter your credentials below. 

{{DatabaseLoginForm|

Studies on the recent religious group, last checked: March 9, 2024. 

The star '''Hylophage-66''' has been confirmed as a central object of veneration for a specific group of survivors inhabiting the level. Initially consisting of approximately eight members, the group has since expanded significantly and shows hostility toward other wanderers.

This recently established religious faction, self-identified as '''Aeternalis Flos Noctis,''' has shown rapid growth recently. Attempts at negotiation or establishing amicable relations have been consistently rejected, confirming the group's high hostility. Reports indicate a marked increase in attacks targeting other wanderers.

At present, all information regarding the origin, motives, and objectives remains completely unknown. In the current state, avoiding any interaction with members of this group is strongly advised. For the time being, what can be done is to wait and perhaps try possible peaceful negotiations in the future. 

}}
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>

<div style="background-color:#000000; color: white; margin:1em; padding:20px 20px; border:4px solid #ff69b4; border-radius: 30px"><span style="color:#ff69b4;"><span style="font-family:Pacifico;">

<center>
<span style="font-size:25px; font-family:Pacifico; text-shadow: 0em 0em 1.0em #ff69b4, 0em 0em 1.0em black;


 background: linear-gradient(90deg, #ff69b4, #e0569d, #ff69b4, #e0569d, #ff69b4);

             background-size: 400%; 
             -webkit-background-clip: text;
             -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
             animation: gradient 5s infinite;"> Colonies and Outposts</span>{{Underline|ff69b4}} <center>

<div style="text-align:left;font-family:Georgia;color:#FFFFFF">

Due to the environmental conditions of '''Level 703''', it is not possible to establish colonies or outposts. However, the existence of a single faction within the level is confirmed.


<center>
<span style="font-size:25px; font-family:Pacifico; text-shadow: 0em 0em 1.0em #ff69b4, 0em 0em 1.0em black;
 background: linear-gradient(90deg, #ff69b4, #e0569d, #ff69b4, #e0569d, #ff69b4);
             background-size: 400%; 
             -webkit-background-clip: text;
             -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
             animation: gradient 5s infinite;"> Aeternalis Flos Noctis</span> <center>

''Aeternalis Flos Noctis,'' a group known for venerating The Star, is a group with a constantly increasing number of members. This faction is most of the time hostile and tends to attack any other wanderers present at '''Level 703'''. Their religious faith is enormous and rigorous, persecuting individuals who refuse to accept it.
This group is not friendly and does not accept trades and sales, but accepts new members who want to venerate the star and join its religion.

Not much is known about their religion. What is possible to know is that the star is their god, and for them, the radiation is a blessing for all the beings at the level. Typically members of this group wear large black clothes and tunics that cover their entire face. Some of these clothes have a symbol, possibly created by them to identify themselves. The same symbol can also be seen on flags that some members carry.

[[File:Saint2.png|center|310x310px]]

Members of this group seem, in an unexplained way, to have "resistance" to radiation and spiritual forces, thus being able to establish themselves within '''divine galleries.''' 
The reason for these attributes is completely unknown and will possibly never be explained, as it was never possible to communicate with any member of the faction.

More information about this faction is still unknown.
{{Underline|ff69b4}}

Please keep in mind that the document below is confidential and can only be read by authorized personnel.

<div style="background-color:white; color:#AAAAAA; margin:1em; padding:5px 10px; border:2px solid #000000; border-radius: 3px">
